import json,urllib.request,urllib.error
TOKEN='edeb8394ced17e30f0e07bc2176bb02405154cc6372c443ed980435503205e1c'
base='http://localhost:8929/api/v4/projects/13/issues'
objs=json.load(open('/tmp/issues.json'))
if not objs:
    print('No issues found')
for obj in objs:
    iid=str(obj['iid'])
    url=base+'/'+iid
    req=urllib.request.Request(url, method='DELETE', headers={'Authorization':'Bearer '+TOKEN})
    try:
        with urllib.request.urlopen(req) as r:
            print('Deleted issue', iid, 'status', r.status)
    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:
        body = e.read().decode() if e.fp else ''
        print('Failed to delete', iid, e.code, body)
PY
